 449:src/voice.h   **** // ŌöĆŌöĆ Voice 6: electric guitar power chord ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ
 450:src/voice.h   **** //   A driven sawtooth power chord ŌĆö each note is a root + fixed perfect fifth +
 451:src/voice.h   **** //   octave-up jangle over a saw octave-down body, so it plays as a chord like a
 452:src/voice.h   **** //   rock guitar. Heavy-ish drive adds overdrive crunch; the filter sits a touch
 453:src/voice.h   **** //   above the fundamental and sweeps wide open with pressure (dig in = bright,
 454:src/voice.h   **** //   pick-attack bite), with resonance for a vocal amp "quack". A fast pitch-env
 455:src/voice.h   **** //   "twang" + a little pick-grit noise on the onset, then amp decay-to-silence
 456:src/voice.h   **** //   (decay_ms/sustain below) so each note plucks and rings out over ~1.2 s while
 457:src/voice.h   **** //   held ŌĆö like a struck string, not an organ. Quantized to a major scale so
 458:src/voice.h   **** //   tapped chords land in key. For a BASS guitar instead: drop freq_low/high ~┬Į,
 459:src/voice.h   **** //   cut drive to ~1.5, use WAVE_TRI, and raise `sustain` if you want it to hold.
ARM GAS  /tmp/claude-502/cceToCIK.s 			page 46


